        {
            "id": 1,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "COVID-19 can affect the hematopoietic system . <S>",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "Thrombocytopenia at admission was prevalent ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "while late - phase or delayed - phase thrombocytopenia",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "( occurred 14 days after symptom onset )",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "is obscure . <S>",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "This retrospective single - center study screened 450 COVID-19 patients",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "and enrolled 271 patients at the Union Hospital , Wuhan , China , from January 25th to March 9th , 2020 . <S>",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "COVID-19 associated delayed - phase thrombocytopenia occurred in 11.8 % percent of enrolling patients . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "The delayed - phase thrombocytopenia in COVID-19 is prone to develop in elderly patients or patients with low lymphocyte count on admission . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "The delayed - phase thrombocytopenia is significantly associated with increased length of hospital stay and higher mortality rate . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "Delayed - phase nadir platelet counts demonstrated a significantly negative correlation with B cell percentages . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "We also presented bone marrow aspiration pathology of three patients with delayed - phase thrombocytopenia ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 12,
            "text": "showing impaired maturation of megakaryocytes . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 15,
            "text": "We speculated",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "that immune mediated platelet destruction might account for the delayed - phase thrombocytopenia in a group of patients . <S>",
            "relation": "FINDINGS"
        },
        {
            "id": 16,
            "parent": 15,
            "text": "Besides , clinicians need to pay attention to the delayed - phase thrombocytopenia especially at 3 - 4 weeks after symptom onset . <S> <P>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        }
    ]
